well_activity_remarks_html:
WELL_NAME API12 WAR_START_DT TEXT_REMARK
0 001 608084003400 2013-03-13 3/13/2013 - Rig arrived on location at 19:00 hrs. Commenced BOP stump testing; 250 low; 1500 psi high for 5 mins each on USBR (good test). 3/14/2013 - RU 36" casing equipment. PU and run 36" shoe joint and one joint of 36" conductor to 82'. MU and run 36" conductor pipe from 41' to 243'. PU and run 36" crossover joint from 206' to 243'. RD 36" crossover running tool. PU and run 36" wellhead joint from 243' to 320'. RD wellhead joint running tool. RD casing tongs. PU and MU CADA tool. 3/15/2013 - MU top drive. Position CADA tool. MU CADA tool to LPWH. Run in with 36" conductor pipe from 322' to 380'. RIH with 36" conductor pipe and jetting assembly to 4759'. Begin tripping in from 4759' to 4938'. Slack off from 4938' and tag mudline at 4941'. Spud well at 15:27 hours. Spud in conductor to 4955' with no pumps. Continue jetting in 36" conductor from 4955' to 5131'. Offline: Performing ROV function testing using topside test unit. 3/16/2013 - Continue jetting in 36" conductor from 5131' to 5253'. Offline: Stump testing BOP's. Held final jetting weight on string and wait for visibility to clear for ROV to confirm stickup of wellhead and retrieve bullseye readings. Confirmed wellhead stickup at 11'. Achieved 3.5 hours of soak time has been achieved. 36" shoe set at 5253'. Released CADA tool. Drilled 26" x 32-1/2" hole from 5253' to 5800'.
1 001 608084003400 2013-03-17 3/17/2013 - Drill from 5800' to 6670' (Section TD). Offline subsea continuing BOP stump testing. Circulate 10.4 ppg pad mud behind fluid caliper. Pumped a total of 2813 bbls 10.4 ppg pad mud. Pump and spot 100 bbls of 16.4 ppg at 6670'. POH to 5253'. Monitor flow; ROV monitored wellhead for 15 minutes (no flow). Release CADA tool. Drop 2.5" activation ball for PBL sub. Pull up to position PBL sub at wellhead. Wash 28" profile and wellhead. POH. PU Dril-Quip tool; set in rotary and install single joint of 6-5/8" ppg drill pipe. 3/18/2013 - RU 28" casing equipment. PU and run 28" casing to 1570'. RD casing equipment. RU 6-5/8" pipe handling equipment. LD hanger joint. 3/19/2013 - RIH with inner string from surface to 1346'. RIH with casing on landing string to 4856'. Stab in wellhead with 28" casing. Continue RIH with 28" casing to 6509'. PU cement head. Land out with 150k down. Perform overpull test to 50K over. Circulate at 6509' with 10.4 ppg. Mix and pump 810 bbls base lead (4181 sacks) of 16.4 ppg Class H foamed cement (6148 cu ft). Mix and pump 227 bbls (1116 sacks) of Class H tail cement (1275 cu ft). Total cement 7423 cu ft. LD cement head. POH. Attached are third party lab test reports for the 28" casing lead and tail cement. 3/20/2013 - POH with 28" casing running tool and LD same. Finish POH with inner string. LD 26" x 32-1/2" BHA. LD 6-5/8" 44# drill pipe. PU 6-5/8" 39# drill pipe. 3/21/2013 - Continue to PU 6-5/8" drill pipe. PU 6-5/8" landing string. Slip and cut drill line. MU BHA #2 and TIH to 1340'. Offline subsea continuing BOP stump testing and preparing for accumulator drawdown test. Perform shallow test with MWD (good test). TIH to 4933'. Stab into wellhead at 2400 hours and TIH to 4976'. 3/22/2013 - TIH from 6187'. Wash from 6187' to 6416'. Tagged cement at 6416' with 20K down. Displace with 10.4 ppg SBM at 6416'. Drill out cement from 6416' to 6509'. Drill out shoe at 6509' and continue drilling ahead to 6670'. Drill from 6670' to 6993'. Notice abnormal noise from derrick drilling machine (DDM) and have mechanics inspect same. POH into 28" shoe from 6993' to 6456' for further inspection of DDM. Troubleshooting indicated the pinion shaft bearing on the DDM was failing. POH from 6456' to 4707'. Offline subsea completed accumulator drawdown test on BOP system and drift tested BOP. Prepared to perform BOP function test; which is the final item to complete the BOP stump testing. Prepare DDM to change out pinion shaft bearing. POH to 97'. 3/23/2013 - Lay out BHA from 97' to surface. Assist mechanics drain oil from derrick drilling machine gear box. Assist electricians and mechanics prepare to remove aft motor on derrick drilling machine. Offload 22" casing.
2 001 608084003400 2013-03-24 3/24/2013 - Complete repairs to DDM and test same. Start PU 26" drilling BHA. Offline: Subsea soak testing BOP and preparing to stump test on 5-7/8" test joint. 3/25/2013 - Continue PU 26" BHA. TIH to 6858'. Wash from 6858' to 6993'. Drill from 6993' to 8146'. 3/26/2013 - Drill from 8146' to 9095'. 3/27/2013 - Drill from 9095' to 9163'. well_activity_remarks_dict.TEXT_REMARK:
3/13/2013 - Rig arrived on location at 19:00 hrs.  Commenced BOP stump testing; 250 low; 1500 psi high for 5 mins each on USBR (good test).

3/14/2013 - RU 36" casing equipment.  PU and run 36" shoe joint and one joint of 36" conductor to 82'.  MU and run 36" conductor pipe from 41' to 243'.  PU and run 36" crossover joint from 206' to 243'.  RD 36" crossover running tool.  PU and run 36" wellhead joint from 243' to 320'.  RD wellhead joint running tool.  RD casing tongs.  PU and MU CADA tool.  

3/15/2013 - MU top drive.  Position CADA tool.  MU CADA tool to LPWH.  Run in with 36" conductor pipe from 322' to 380'.  RIH with 36" conductor pipe and jetting assembly to 4759'.  Begin tripping in from 4759' to 4938'.  Slack off from 4938' and tag mudline at 4941'.  Spud well at 15:27 hours.  Spud in conductor to 4955' with no pumps.  Continue jetting in 36" conductor from 4955' to 5131'.  Offline: Performing ROV function testing using topside test unit.

3/16/2013 - Continue jetting in 36" conductor from 5131' to 5253'.  Offline: Stump testing BOP's.  Held final jetting weight on string and wait for visibility to clear for ROV to confirm stickup of wellhead and retrieve bullseye readings.  Confirmed wellhead stickup at 11'.  Achieved 3.5 hours of soak time has been achieved.  36" shoe set at 5253'.  Released CADA tool.  Drilled 26" x 32-1/2" hole from 5253' to 5800'.

3/17/2013 - Drill from 5800' to 6670' (Section TD).  Offline subsea continuing BOP stump testing.  Circulate 10.4 ppg pad mud behind fluid caliper.  Pumped a total of 2813 bbls 10.4 ppg pad mud.  Pump and spot 100 bbls of 16.4 ppg at 6670'.  POH to 5253'.  Monitor flow; ROV monitored wellhead for 15 minutes (no flow).  Release CADA tool.  Drop 2.5" activation ball for PBL sub.  Pull up to position PBL sub at wellhead.  Wash 28" profile and wellhead.  POH.  PU Dril-Quip tool; set in rotary and install single joint of 6-5/8" ppg drill pipe.  

3/18/2013 - RU 28" casing equipment.  PU and run 28" casing to 1570'.  RD casing equipment.  RU 6-5/8" pipe handling equipment.  LD hanger joint.  

3/19/2013 - RIH with inner string from surface to 1346'.  RIH with casing on landing string to 4856'.  Stab in wellhead with 28" casing.  Continue RIH with 28" casing to 6509'.  PU cement head.  Land out with 150k down.  Perform overpull test to 50K over.  Circulate at 6509' with 10.4 ppg.  Mix and pump 810 bbls base lead (4181 sacks) of 16.4 ppg Class H foamed cement (6148 cu ft).  Mix and pump 227 bbls (1116 sacks) of Class H tail cement (1275 cu ft).  Total cement 7423 cu ft.  LD cement head.  POH.  Attached are third party lab test reports for the 28" casing lead and tail cement. 

3/20/2013 - POH with 28" casing running tool and LD same.  Finish POH with inner string.  LD 26" x 32-1/2"  BHA.  LD 6-5/8" 44# drill pipe.  PU 6-5/8" 39# drill pipe.

3/21/2013 - Continue to PU 6-5/8" drill pipe.  PU 6-5/8" landing string.  Slip and cut drill line.  MU BHA #2 and TIH to 1340'.  Offline subsea continuing BOP stump testing and preparing for accumulator drawdown test.  Perform shallow test with MWD (good test).  TIH to 4933'.  Stab into wellhead at 2400 hours and TIH to 4976'.  

3/22/2013 - TIH from 6187'.  Wash from 6187' to 6416'.  Tagged cement at 6416' with 20K down.  Displace with 10.4 ppg SBM at 6416'.  Drill out cement from 6416' to 6509'.  Drill out shoe at 6509' and continue drilling ahead to 6670'.  Drill from 6670' to 6993'.  Notice abnormal noise from derrick drilling machine (DDM) and have mechanics inspect same.  POH into 28" shoe from 6993' to 6456' for further inspection of DDM.  Troubleshooting indicated the pinion shaft bearing on the DDM was failing.  POH from 6456' to 4707'.  Offline subsea completed accumulator drawdown test on BOP system and drift tested BOP.  Prepared to perform BOP function test; which is the final item to complete the BOP stump testing. Prepare DDM to change out pinion shaft bearing.  POH to 97'.

3/23/2013 - Lay out BHA from 97' to surface.  Assist mechanics drain oil from derrick drilling machine gear box.  Assist electricians and mechanics prepare to remove aft motor on derrick drilling machine.  Offload 22" casing.

3/24/2013 - Complete repairs to DDM and test same.  Start PU 26" drilling BHA.  Offline: Subsea soak testing BOP and preparing to stump test on 5-7/8" test joint.

3/25/2013 - Continue PU 26" BHA.  TIH to 6858'.  Wash from 6858' to 6993'.  Drill from 6993' to 8146'.  

3/26/2013 - Drill from 8146' to 9095'.  

3/27/2013 - Drill from 9095' to 9163'.  Pump 100 bbls of 11 ppg sweep with green dye to calibrate hole for wash out followed by 11 ppg SSWBM and circulate 1-1/2 hole volume at 1200 gpm with 1650 psi.  Spot 33 bbls of 16.4 ppg SSWBM out of string at 9163'.  POOH with 26" drilling BHA from 9147' to 6454'.  Monitored well for flow; well static.  Wash inside wellhead with seawater from 4938' to 4928'.  Wash around wellhead.  POOH with BHA to surface.

3/28/2013 - RU 22" casing handling equipment.  Run 22" casing from 34' to 2025'.  

3/29/2013 - Run 22" casing from 2025' to 4183'.  PU 22" cross over joint and 27" wellhead.  TIH with 6-5/8" drillpipe from surface to 3906'.  MU HPWH to MRLD. 

3/30/2013 - PU 6-5/8" drillpipe and RIH to 4546'.  TIH with 22" casing on 6-5/8" drillpipe from 4515' to 4880'.  Circulate with SW.  Stab 22" shoe into LPWH at 4933'.  Wash with SW at 4942'.  TIH with 22" casing on 6-5/8" landing string.  TIH to 6418'.  Displace drillsting with 11.0 ppg mud.  TIH from 5021' to 6418'.  MU DDM and fill landing string with 11.0 ppg mud.  TIH with 22" casing on 6-5/8" landing string to 9114'.  Land out HPWH into LPWH.  Circulate 1.5 annulus volume at 9114'.  Break circulation with cement unit and test lines.

3/31/2013 - Attempt to cement 22" casing.  Abort cement job due to Bulk Cement System unable to deliver cement at a controlled rate for mix and pump.  Displace cement out of drillstring with 11.0 ppg SSWBM.  Troubleshoot cement delivery system.  Circulate 50 bbls of 11.0 ppg SSWBM at 300 GPM with 60 psi every hour to verify circulation.

4/1/2013 - Cement 22" casing.  Mix and pump 9051 cu ft of 16.4 ppg Class H lead foamed cement.  Mix and pump 848 cu ft of 16.4 ppg Class H tail spacer.  Total cement pumped is 9899 cu ft.  Cement confirmation lab test results for 22" casing are attached to the WAR.  Released dart and began displacing with SW.  RD cement head.  Pump 1.5 drill string volume of SW.  POOH with 6-5/8" landing string and MRLD assembly.

4/2/2013 - POOH with 6-5/8" landing string to surface.  Perform slip and cut operations.  Notice 5 bolts were sheared on drill line grove split sleeve on drawworks drum while slipping on new drill line.  Slip and cut 124' of drill line.  RU riser handling equipment.  Decision made to remove and change out all bots on drill line grove split sleeve.  Remove sheared bolts on drawworks drum line groove plates.  

4/3/2013 - Remove sheared bolts on drawworks drum line split sleeve.

4/4/2013 - Remove Lebus split sleeve from drawworks.  Remove the sheared bolts from draw works drum.  Spool drill line on drawworks.  RU hydraulic hoses to riser running tool.  PU 1-slick joint of riser and RIH 75'.  

4/5/2013 - Skid BOP's on transporter to well center and connect double to BOP.  Lift BOP from transporter.  Run BOP to 210'; BOP in splash zone at 0415 hours.  Secure BOP transporter and under hull guides in stowed position.  Pressure test choke and kill lines.  Pressure test rigid conduit and boost lines.  Continue running riser to 1710'.

4/6/2013 - Continue to run BOP on riser to 3210'.  Pressure test choke and kill line.  Pressure test rigid conduit lines and boost line.  Continue to run BOP on riser to 4785'.  PU slid joint; 10' spacer and landing joint; BOP depth 4874'.

4/7/2013 - Land on wellhead with 60K down.  Latched up at 0835 hours.  Perform overpull on wellhead with 60K.  Perform acoustic test.  Perform wellhead connector test against upper blind shear rams (good test).  Perform deadman/autoshear test.  RD riser running tool.  PU diverter running tool and MU test plug.  

4/8/2013 - Install diverter test tool and test to 500 psi (good test).  RD diverter test tool.  MU BOP test assembly and TIH to 1395'.  MU dual cam tool.  Continue RIH to 5834'.  Wash wellhead from 4925' to 4935'.  RIH with BOP test assembly to 6047'.  PU double dutch testing assembly.  RU Chicksan lines to double dutch assembly.  Break circulation with cement unit.

4/9/2013 - Perform BOP test.  RIH from 6047' to 6371'.  Land out BOP test tool in wellhead.  Continue BOP test.  Engage dual cam mandrel into bowl.  POOH from 6264' to 4700'.  

4/10/2013 - POOH with dual cam tool and test assembly.  LD bull nose sub.  Function diverter.  Pressure test choke and kill manifold (good test).  Pressure test 22" casing to 4660 psi (good test).  Received approval from Jarvis Outlaw via email to continue with drilling operations with piston seal leak present in casing shear ram open function and malfunctioning yellow pod subsea flow meter. Copy of email attached to WAR.  

4/11/2013 - PU 6-5/8" drill pipe and RIH to 5228'.  Set wear sleeve.  TIH with 18.125" x 21" BHA to 6720'.  Perform accumulator draw down test.  Continue TIH with 18.125" x 21" BHA to 8709'.  Washed from 8709' to 8728' and located 16" profile with upper rhino reamer.  Worked reamer through 16" profile.  Continue TIH with 18.125" x 21" BHA from 8709' to 8907' and tagged up with upper rhino reamer on 18" profile at 8795'.  

4/12/2013 - Attempt to work upper rhino reamer through 18" profile with no success.  POOH with 18.125" x 21" drilling assembly.  LD and inspect rhino XS reamer cement (unpinned) and rhino XS reamer (pinned).  PU and inspect bit.  RIH with 18.125" x 21" BHA to 1095'.  TIH with 21" under reamer and casing reamer to 4930'.  Set wear sleeve at 4930'.  Continue TIH with 18.125" x 21" BHA.

4/13/2013 - Displace choke; kill and boost lines with 11.5 ppg SOBM.  Displaced hole with 3145 bbls SOBM.  Attempted to wash through cement at 8907' with no success.  Wash and ream ratty cement from 8907' to 9000'.  Drill soft to firm cement from 9000' to 9017'.  Drill firm cement from 9017' to 9100'.  CBU while troubleshooting derrick drilling machine (DDM) aft motor bearing.  Pump 40 bbls of 13.6 ppg slug and chase with 10 bbls of 11.5 ppg SOBM.

4/14/2013 - Troubleshoot DDM.  POOH with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling assembly.  Pull wear sleeve at 5330'.  TIH with drill collars.  RIH with 6-5/8" landing string.  Perform diagnostics on DDM.  Repair DDM.

4/15/2013 - Remove motor #2 on DDM.  TOOH with drill pipe and drill collars.  Performed vibration sound test on DDM.  Service dual cam tool.  PU 18-1/8" x 21" BHA and TIH with same.

4/16/2013 - TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" BHA.  Offload 18" casing.  Prepare to install DDM motor #2.  Offload 2000 bbls of 16.0 ppg SOBM.  

4/17/2013 - Complete installation of DDM drive motor #2.  TIH with 18-1/8" x 21" drilling BHA to 6284'.  Function test BOP's.  TIH to 8978'.  Wash down to 9100'.  Drill cement from 9100' to 9163'.  Drill 10' of new formation to 9173'.  Perform FIT test.  Surface measured formation pressure integrity test = 14.25 ppg; downhole measured formation pressure integrity test = 14.49 ppg.  Surface measured LOT = 14.18 ppg; downhole measured LOT = 14.42 ppg.  

4/18/2013 - Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 9173' to 9295'.  TIH to 9220'.  Drop ball and shear pins to open reamer.  Pull test against shoe.  Ream down from 9206' to 9295'.  Drill and ream from 9295' to 9766'.

4/19/2013 - Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 9766' to 9888'.  Check flow (4 BPH loss).  Drill from 9888' to 9996'.  Pull to shoe to diagnose wellhead movement.  Increase tensioner setting.  Wash down to 9996'.  Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 9996' to 10191'.  

4/20/2013 - Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 10191' to 10287'.  Circulate while repairing flow out sensors.  Drill from 10287' to 10310'.  Circulate while repairing flow out sensors.  Drill 18-1/8" x 21" hole from 10310' to 11084' while increasing mud weight to 12.4 ppg.

4/21/2013 - Drill to 11406'.  CBU at 11406'.  Pump 40 bbls slug and chase with 10 bbls of 12.4 SOBM.  TOH from 11406' to 9091'.  Circulate at shoe.

4/22/2013 - TIH from 9091' to 11268'.  Wash down from 11268' to 11404'.  Drill ahead to 12180'.  Weighted up to 12.8 ppg downhole mud weight.  

4/23/2013 - Drill to 13010' (section TD).  Circulate 1-1/2 times bottoms up.

4/24/2013 - Pump 61 bbls of 16.1 ppg pad mud and spot same at 13010'.  RU BOP test assembly.  Test BOP's.  TOOH to 4588'.  Function test upper; lower and casing shear rams.  

4/25/2013 - Function test diverter commencing at 00:30 hours.  See attached email from Jarvis Outlaw; BSEE; confirming acceptance that the function test due 4/24 commenced 30 minutes into 4/25 immediately following continuous BOP testing and functioning operations.  TIH to 4940'.  Pump 100 bbls hi-vis sweep and circulate out same.  TOOH to 4667'.  RD BOP test equipment.  Pump 25 bbls slug.  Slip and cut 127' of drill line.  RU casing equipment.

4/26/2013 - Run 18" liner to 4030'.  MU hanger joint.  RD casing equipment.

4/27/2013 - RU to run inner string.  TIH with inner string to 3676' (casing shoe at 4052').  MU running tool and seal assembly.  MU flowback tool.  Run casing on 6-5/8" drill pipe from 4780' to 5184'.

4/28/2013 - TIH with landing string to 12;817'.  Circulated 1.5 times bottoms up.  Cemented 18" casing with 1;820 cu.ft. 16.4 ppg class H cement.

4/29/2013 - Released running tool.  Set seal assembly and pressure tested same.  TOOH w/ inner string to surface

4/30/2013 - Closed LBSRs and tested 18" liner.  Function tested BOPs.  PU 16-1/2" x 20" BHA and TIH to 3;561'.
